sec.p:
The study was approved by the Regional Ethics Review Board, Gothenburg, Sweden (dnr 615–08) and permission was obtained from the director of each SU. The FGIs were carried out in accordance with the Helsinki Declaration;
31
 where oral and written information was given to each participant and informed consent was obtained. The voluntary nature of participation and the possibility to withdraw without prejudice was explained to the participants. Confidential handling of the data to protect the identity of participants from those outside the FGIs was ensured but the participants were made aware that it would not be possible to create confidentiality within the FGIs.
